    "en": {
      "title": "Change in Earth's rotation speed after 50 years",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Scientists say Earth is spinning faster than it did 50 years ago. In that way, Earth completes its one-day cycle in less than 24 hours.",
        "It is a scientific fact that the earth rotates in its orbit and revolves around the sun in 365 days.",
        "Earth takes 365 days to orbit the Sun once and 24 hours to orbit itself.",
        "That means scientists have discovered that there is a one-second variation in rotation speed. Scientists say that the change in the Earth's rotation speed is caused by various factors such as the Earth's core, the oceans, the movement of the atmosphere and the gravitational pull of the Moon.",
        "On July 29, Earth broke its record for the shortest day. It was considered the shortest month since 1960.",
        "On July 29, Earth recorded its shortest day. This again revealed that the earth rotates rapidly.",
        "On July 19, 2020, the Earth rotated so fast that it completed one day in less than 24 hours. That means Earth completed its rotation 1.47 milliseconds earlier.",
        "In this situation, yesterday the Earth completed its one-day rotation 1.59 milliseconds earlier. Scientists have predicted that next year the earth will rotate faster than this and break this record. (R)"
      ],
